Mini Project: Student Portfolio Website
Problem Statement

Create a Student Portfolio Website using HTML to showcase your personal, academic, and professional information. The website should act as a digital portfolio that introduces you, highlights your skills, achievements, projects, and provides contact details.

The webpage must be developed using only the HTML concepts learned so far, including headings, paragraphs, comments, and text formatting tags.

Objective

To design a structured and well-formatted personal portfolio webpage that demonstrates your understanding of HTML basics and text formatting elements.

Requirements

The webpage should contain the following sections:

1. Home Section
Student Name
Profile Title (e.g., Student, Developer, Designer)
Welcome Message
2. About Me
Brief self-introduction
Career objective
Personal interests and hobbies
3. Education
Academic qualifications
College/School details
Current course and year
4. Skills
Technical Skills
Soft Skills
Areas of Interest
5. Projects
List at least 2 academic or personal projects
Brief description of each project
6. Achievements
Certifications
Awards
Competitions participated in
7. Contact Information
Email Address
Phone Number
City/Location
